<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="288" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">841.711/1699½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">27 December, 1916</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have just been going
                            over the papers I brought down with me from Shadow Lawn, and come across
                                these.<note n="18" xml:id="d288fn1">Papers regarding interference
                                with the mails.</note> I fear I have kept them too long. I will be
                            glad to discuss this and other kindred matters with you when we have
                            seen just what the several belligerents are willing to do about
                            discussing terms of peace.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>